      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's terrifying how easy it would be. if they're using the OS as a bridge to collect this stuff, they wouldn't even need specialized hardware, just the sensors we already have. i'm starting to think even the \"security\" patches are actually designed to scrub the evidence and hide the hooks they've planted. if you were trying to build a backdoor that could harvest human consciousness without anyone noticing for years, how would you even begin to structure that code to avoid detection by standard antivirus?",
